docs.lead_paragraph: Derek Chauvin has been found guilty of the murder of George Floyd. But whatever bittersweet feelings the rare outcome elicited were short-lived, since instances of police brutality compound almost daily. There’s no debate: Policing is broken in America. But how do we fix it?

headline.main: Policing Is Not Broken. It’s ‘Literally Designed to Work in This Way.’

docs.abstract: Despite being tipped that “Congress itself is the target” on Jan. 6, Capitol Police were ordered not to use their most powerful crowd-control weapons, according to a scathing new watchdog report.
docs.snippet: Despite being tipped that “Congress itself is the target” on Jan. 6, Capitol Police were ordered not to use their most powerful crowd-control weapons, according to a scathing new watchdog report.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Capitol Police had clearer advance warnings about the Jan. 6 attack than were previously known, including the potential for violence in which “Congress itself is the target.” But officers were instructed by their leaders not to use their most aggressive tactics to hold off the mob, according to a scathing new report by the agency’s internal investigator.

headline.main: Capitol Police Told to Hold Back on Riot Response on Jan. 6, Report Finds
headline.print_headline: Report Pins Failures of Jan. 6 On Capitol Police Preparation

docs.abstract: The Ethical Society of Police isn’t afraid to speak out against police misconduct.
docs.snippet: The Ethical Society of Police isn’t afraid to speak out against police misconduct.
docs.lead_paragraph: This week, a veteran officer in Brooklyn Center, Minn., killed an unarmed man, claiming to have mistaken her gun for her Taser. The Ethical Society of Police, a St. Louis group consisting mostly of Black officers, was quick to comment on the shooting, calling out the negligence of the officer.

headline.main: I’m in a Police Union That Holds Bad Cops Accountable
